This press briefing took place in December 2017 and covered various topics, including the Trump administration's accomplishments in its first year, particularly in the areas of legislation, tax cuts, energy independence, deregulation, and judicial appointments. The officials also discussed the repeal of the individual mandate under the Affordable Care Act, the fight against ISIS, American energy independence, the recognition of Jerusalem as the capital of Israel, the opioid crisis, and veterans' issues. They expressed optimism about bipartisan cooperation in 2018, particularly on issues such as DACA and infrastructure. The officials also mentioned the possibility of welfare reform and the importance of results and accomplishments to the Trump administration.